article.description: — Max Brooks had 19 points, eight rebounds and three blocks and Ayinde Hikim posted 17 points as UMass Lowell beat Hartford 85-75 on Monday night.
article.headline: Brooks leads UMass Lowell past Hartford 85-75
article.linkText: Brooks leads UMass Lowell past Hartford 85-75
article.story: LOWELL, Mass. -- — Max Brooks had 19 points, eight rebounds and three blocks and Ayinde Hikim posted 17 points as UMass Lowell beat Hartford 85-75 on Monday night. Brooks hit 8 of 10 shots. Allin Blunt had 10 points for UMass Lowell (12-10, 4-6 America East Conference). Hunter Marks had 19 points and five assists for the Hawks (5-15, 3-5). Moses Flowers added 16 points and D.J. Mitchell had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
